    "Nevertheless, establishing the most suitable threshold poses challenges and tends to differ for various synergy measures.",
    "For instance, GraphSynergy (Yang et al. 2021) uses the threshold of zero to binarize Loewe measure with a score greater than or less than 0 indicating a synergistic or non-synergistic effect, respectively.",
    "Zhang et al.",
    "(Zhang et al. 2023), on the other hand, categorized Loewe and ZIP synergistic scores using quartiles.",
    "The highest quartile represents synergistic effects, and the lowest quartile represents antagonistic effects."
